From: Timo Könnecke <mo@mowerk.net>
Date: Thu, 19 Jun 2026 22:15:25 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] nitrous: wire bluesleep_hci_event into existing wake mechanism

The nitrous driver requires hci_ldisc.c's bluesleep_hci_event() symbol
to link, but provides no implementation of its own (unlike bass's
bcm_bluesleep driver, which both provides and uses this hook). A prior
revision of this patch added an empty stub purely to satisfy the
linker, which left Bluetooth low-power sleep effectively disabled.

hci_ldisc.c calls bluesleep_hci_event(HCI_DEV_WRITE) on every outgoing
HCI write. With an empty stub, nothing ever asserts dev-wake-gpio
before a write, so the BT chip is never woken for outgoing UART
traffic. This routes the call into nitrous's own existing
nitrous_wake_device_locked() wake path instead of doing nothing.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [nemo-specific port patch]

The nitrous driver requires hci_ldisc.c's bluesleep_hci_event() symbol
to link, but provides no implementation of its own (unlike bass's
bcm_bluesleep driver, which both provides and uses this hook). A prior
session added an empty stub purely to satisfy the linker.

hci_ldisc.c calls bluesleep_hci_event(HCI_DEV_WRITE) on every outgoing
HCI write. With an empty stub, nothing ever asserts dev-wake-gpio
before a write, so the BT chip is never woken for outgoing UART
traffic, including the initial patchram handshake. This routes the
call into nitrous's own existing nitrous_wake_device_locked() wake
path instead of doing nothing.

diff --git a/drivers/bluetooth/nitrous.c b/drivers/bluetooth/nitrous.c
index d994958..98ce5f1 100644
--- a/drivers/bluetooth/nitrous.c
+++ b/drivers/bluetooth/nitrous.c
@@ -20,7 +20,7 @@
  * The current implementation is very specific to Qualcomm serial driver
  * with BCM chipset.
  */
-
+#define HCI_DEV_WRITE 7
 #include <linux/delay.h>
 #include <linux/gpio.h>
 #include <linux/hrtimer.h>
@@ -567,3 +567,16 @@ module_exit(nitrous_exit);
 MODULE_DESCRIPTION("Nitrous Oxide Driver for Bluetooth");
 MODULE_AUTHOR("Google");
 MODULE_LICENSE("GPL");
+
+void bluesleep_hci_event(unsigned long event)
+{
+	unsigned long flags;
+	if (!bt_lpm)
+		return;
+	if (event == HCI_DEV_WRITE) {
+		spin_lock_irqsave(&bt_lpm->uart_port->lock, flags);
+		nitrous_wake_device_locked(bt_lpm, true);
+		spin_unlock_irqrestore(&bt_lpm->uart_port->lock, flags);
+	}
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL(bluesleep_hci_event);
